<paragraph id="9D4D36A8FFF7257BFC005299FA78C68B" blockId="6.[919,1408,670,693]" box="[919,1408,670,693]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">
<taxonomicName id="5AF24D2BFFF7257BFC005299FA78C68B" authority="Bond-Buckup and Buckup, 1994" authorityName="Bond-Buckup and Buckup" authorityYear="1994" box="[919,1408,670,693]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aeglidae" genus="Aegla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jarai">
<emphasis id="AF86EABAFFF7257BFC005299FBEAC68B" box="[919,1042,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Aegla jarai</emphasis>
Bond-Buckup and Buckup, 1994
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D4D36A8FFF7257BFCDA52C8FBA3C016" blockId="6.[845,1483,719,1064]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Diagnosis.—Antero-lateral spine of carapace extending beyond middle of cornea; protogastric lobes subtle; rostrum very long in adult males, styliform, carinate along its entire length; anterior angle of ventral margin of epimeron 2 unarmed; outer proximal margin of movable finger of cheliped with lobe tipped with tubercle; palmar crest of cheliped disc-shaped, strongly excavated; inner margin of ventral surface of ischium of cheliped with one conical distal spine and up to three tubercles; dorsal margin of merus of second pereiopod with spine, followed by tubercles; ventral margin of merus of second pereiopod with scaliform tubercles.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D4D36A8FFF7257BFCDA5445FACEC0AA" blockId="6.[845,1482,1090,1172]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">
Formerly Known Distribution.—Brazil: Central and southern part of state of Santa Catarina, and northern part of state of Rio Grande do Sul (
<bibRefCitation id="F9634B59FFF7257BFBDD547AFAD2C0AA" author="Bond-Buckup, G." box="[1098,1322,1149,1172]" editor="G. A. S. Melo" journalOrPublisher="Editora Loyola, Sao Paulo" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" pagination="21 - 116" refId="ref5118" refString="Bond-Buckup, G. 2003. Familia Aeglidae, pp. 21 - 116. In, G. A. S. Melo (ed.), Manual de identificacao dos Crustacea Decapoda, de agua doce do Brasil. Editora Loyola, Sao Paulo." title="Familia Aeglidae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Manual de identificacao dos Crustacea Decapoda, de agua doce do Brasil" year="2003">Bond-Buckup, 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
